Bloemfotein Two women died when two cars collided head-on on the N1 in Bloemfontein on Saturday, Free State paramedics said. When paramedics arrived on the scene they found that two women were still trapped in a &quot;red car&quot; and both had already died, Netcare 911 spokesperson Athlenda Mathe said. &quot;The women were declared dead by Netcare 911 paramedics. The driver of the red vehicle was found to have sustained minor injuries; the patient was transported to a nearby hospital for further medical care. The driver of the white car escaped unharmed.&quot; Netcare 911 paramedics worked alongside paramedics from the provincial emergency medical services (EMS), Mathe said. African News Agency